captions.text:
America's Best Dance Crew's
sixth season is hitting
MTV on April 7.

And Just Dance will keep you in
the know of everything and
anything ABDC.

Let's start with the 10 crews
selected to compete for the
title this year.

Phunk Phenomenon is a
Boston-based coed crew that

blends modern and traditional
styles.

787 Crew is bringing Latin
flavor, flips, and finesse to

ABDC from the sunny island
of Puerto Rico.

Instant Noodles are the sixth
seasons B-boy crew, with roots
throughout Asia.

The ICONic Boyz are the
youngest group.

This New Jersey group was last
seen busting a move on Paula
Abdul's Live to Dance.

The FootworKINGz of Chicago will
be working their footwork

skills and a dance style
that's all new to ABDC.

Jag6ed is an all-girls
contemporary
pole dancing crew.

They combine dance and
acrobatics in a unique
performance art form.

Eclectic Gentlemen from North
Hollywood will bring their

suave and succinct style
to season six.

Street Kingdom from Los Angeles
will keep the krumping
coming all season long.

The hip-hop crew I aM mE has
members from all around the
world who know how to work.

And lastly, ReQuest is an
all-female crew from New

Zealand who fuse cultures
together
through their movement.

Have any questions
for the crews?

Let us know in the comment
box below.

And don't miss the season
premiere of America's Best

Dance Crew on Thursday, April
7 at 10/9 Central on MTV.

title: America's Best Dance Crew Season 6 Crew Line-up
